Leicester City have made a bid of £6.5million for Watford striker Troy Deeney.

The Foxes are hoping to boost their attacking options ahead of the start of the Premier League season, as they return to the top flight for the first time in a decade.

The 26-year-old has been in prolific in the Championship over the previous two seasons - scoring 45 goals for Watford.

