His performances have attracted interest from other Premier League sides, including Leicester's fellow promoted side Burnley.

Deeney spent two-and-a-half months in prison in 2012 after being sentenced for affray for kicking a man in the head during a brawl.

He was released early from his 10-month sentence, after showing remorse and being a first time offender.

